<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/5265333-kimberly-hicks"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1507483217i/5265333._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/5265333-kimberly-hicks">Kimberly Hicks</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Although profanity in books do not bother me, there&apos;s very little in this book thus far. If you&apos;re accustomed to legal thrillers, you couldn&apos;t keep th<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Although profanity in books do not bother me, there's very little in this book thus far. If you're accustomed to legal thrillers, you couldn't keep the realism of the officers of the court intact, if there weren't some profanity. That's how it is in law firms. Lawyers need a release, as does the staff. Having said that profanity is minimal in this story.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
