<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/66499740-steven-mastroyin"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1491054890i/66499740._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/66499740-steven-mastroyin">Steven Mastroyin</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">(This answer contains spoilers to answer the spoiler in the question. Just adding this text until goodreads marks this a spoiler) <br/><br/>Mick didn&apos;t know whe<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">(This answer contains spoilers to answer the spoiler in the question. Just adding this text until goodreads marks this a spoiler) <br /><br />Mick didn't know whether Jennifer had told David that it was Mick that pushed her down the stairs. Presumably, he figured that if David knew, then David was also the one that arranged her actual death and he would want to keep that a secret. Mick's only leverage over David in this situation is the threat of David going to jail. If David is found guilty, he has no reason not to expose Mick.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
