<div id="review_4151496184" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4151496184" />
    <a title="jessica" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10171516-jessica"><img alt="jessica" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1509983330p2/10171516.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4151496184?book_show_action=true">Sep 12, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="jessica" class="user" itemprop="url" name="jessica" href="/user/show/10171516-jessica">jessica</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4151496184" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer464109825589783089">this started off very promising and actually had me really hooked. but then things just kind of fall apart as the story progresses.<br/><br/>i will say that when it comes to the legal details of this story (the evidence processing, the trial preparation, the hearing strategies, and the actual trial itself), its presented really well. the author is a defense lawyer, so its obvious hes knowledgeable about how the system works and i feel like i actually learned a lot about criminal law, which i really enjoye</span>
  <span id="freeText464109825589783089" style="display:none">this started off very promising and actually had me really hooked. but then things just kind of fall apart as the story progresses.<br /><br />i will say that when it comes to the legal details of this story (the evidence processing, the trial preparation, the hearing strategies, and the actual trial itself), its presented really well. the author is a defense lawyer, so its obvious hes knowledgeable about how the system works and i feel like i actually learned a lot about criminal law, which i really enjoyed. but where the author suffers is with actual storytelling. <br /><br />the narrative is just so… convoluted. the plot is plagued with so much drama, its unbelievable. all the blackmailing and affairs and posturing and affairs and drug crime ring and crooked cops and euthanasia and oh, did i mention all the affairs?? its almost as if the crime being tried, which is murder, gets completely swept to the side. such a shame. and there are times when page after page is spent talking about boring moments in the characters pasts. they have absolutely nothing to do with the current situation and are a really poor attempt at characterisation. <br /><br />i dunno. i really loved how in-depth the criminal law process is discussed in this, but the actual storytelling components are pretty weak. which is probably what is expected from a lawyer turned novelist. <br /><br /><b>↠ <i>3 stars</i></b></span>
  <a data-text-id="464109825589783089" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
